==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Reek
<hw>Reek</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>r⟦emac⟧c</ets>; akin to
OFries. <ets>r⟦emac⟧k</ets>, LG. & D. <ets>rook</ets>, G.
<ets>rauch</ets>, OHG. <ets>rouh</ets>, Dan. <ets>r⟦oum⟧g</ets>, Sw.
<ets>r⟦oum⟧k</ets>, Icel. <ets>reykr</ets>, and to AS.
<ets>re⟦oacute⟧can</ets> to reek, smoke, Icel. <ets>rj⟦umac⟧ka</ets>, G.
<ets>riechen</ets> to smell.]</ety> <def>Vapor; steam; smoke;
fume.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As hateful to me as the <qex>reek</qex> of a limekiln.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Reek
<hw>Reek</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Reeked</conjf> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧kt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Reeking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[As. <ets>r⟦emac⟧can</ets>. See
<er>Reek</er> vapor.]</ety> <def>To emit vapor, usually that which is
warm and moist; to be full of fumes; to steam; to smoke; to
exhale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Few chimneys <qex>reeking</qex> you shall espy.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I found me laid⟦br⟧
In balmy sweat, which with his beams the sun⟦br⟧
Soon dried, and on the <qex>reeking</qex> moisture fed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The coffee rooms <qex>reeked</qex> with tobacco.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reeky</ent>⟦br⟧
